The paper deals with constructing algebraic geometry codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes, and devising efficient encoding and decoding algorithms for them. This falls under the realm of information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also makes use of algebraic structures and Riemann-Roch spaces, which are topics in algebraic geometry (cs.AG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of certain algorithms for polynomial multiplication, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
